data.name: label16.Text
data.value: It is located on the periphery of the marrow and is arranged in the form of cords (funicles) in which we find ascending beams located, generally peripheral, descending, located deep from the previous ones, and bundles, located most deeply, in the immediate vicinity of the gray substance. Between the middle fissure and the anterior horns are the anterior cords; between the posterior median septum, which prolongs the dorsal median trench, and the anterior horns are the posterior cords, and between the anterior and posterior horns are the lateral cords. In these cords are nerve fibers grouped into ascending beams of sensitivity, descendents of motor and bundles of association.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value: They are visible in the lower cervical region (C8), the thoracic region (T1-T12) and the upper lumbar region (L1-L2). They contain Preganglionary sympathetic vegetative neurones whose axons leave the marrow along the ventral root pathway of the spinal nerve and form the preganglional fibers of the sympathetic system. Between the lateral and posterior horns, in the white matter of the marrow is the cross-linked substance of the marrow more individualized in the cervical region and made up of neurones arranged in the network.

data.name: label11.Text
data.value: They contain sensory neurones that have the meaning of deutoneuron (second neurone), the protoneuroon (I neurone) being located in the spinal ganglia. At the deutoneuron level, some of the axons of pseudounipolar neurones (I neurone in the spinal ganglion) are terminated. The sensory neurones in the posterior horns are small, arranged in the form of relatively structured groups called nuclei (the nucleus of the head of the posterior horn, the thoracic nucleus, etc.). The anterior and posterior horns appear on the longitudinal section in the form of columns.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: they contain 2 types of somatomotors: a (alpha) and y (gamma) neurones, whose axons form the ventral root of the spinal nerves. The Axon of neurone a reaches the striated muscle with which it forms a special neuroeffector synapse, called the motor plate, while the Axon of neurone y reaches the peripheral (contractile) portion of the muscle fibers in the structure of the neuromuscular spindle. A neurones and y neurones are multipolar, with their bodies having diameters of 70-150 microns.

data.value: They contain the somatomotor device that is better developed in the region of intumescences (cervical and lumbar). The anterior horns are wider and shorter

data.name: label6.Text
data.value: It shows the ependimar canal containing CSF at the center, which, upwards in the brain stem, expands to form the IV ventricle. It also dilates in the terminal portion of the marrow, forming, at the level of the terminal filum, the V-ventricle, also called the terminal ventricle.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: It is made up of the body of neurones. The cross bar of the “H” forms the gray Commission of the marrow, and the lateral portions of the “H” are subdivided into horns: Anterior, lateral and posterior.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: The marrow consists of gray matter arranged in the center, having the appearance of the letter “H”, and white substance, on the periphery, in the form of cords (funicles).
